HEADWORD: Fasces
<hw>Fas"ces</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.,
<pos>pl.</pos> of <ets>fascis</ets> bundle; cf. <ets>fascia</ets> a
band, and Gr. <grk>fa`kelos</grk> a bundle.]</ety>, <fld>(Rom.
Antiq.)</fld> <def>A bundle of rods, having among them an ax with the
blade projecting, borne before the Roman magistrates as a badge of their
authority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

